    "question_id": "Q4",
    "framework": "AFME",
    "text": "Has your regulator raised any material issues in respect of your banking, custody and client money activities within the last 12 months?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "BNY and its subsidiaries are routinely subject to governmental and regulatory examinations, information-gathering requests, investigations, and proceedings (both formal and informal) in the ordinary course of business [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-25-000118::PART_II.Item_6#0168]. Claims for significant monetary damages are often asserted in legal actions, while claims for disgorgement, restitution, penalties, and/or other remedial actions or sanctions may be sought in governmental and regulatory matters [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-24-000133::PART_II.Item_6#0174]. However, on the basis of BNY's current knowledge and understanding, management does not believe that judgments, settlements, or orders arising from these matters \u2014 either individually or in the aggregate, after giving effect to applicable reserves and insurance coverage \u2014 will have a material adverse effect [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-24-000133::PART_II.Item_6#0174]. As of March 31, 2026, BNY did not record any material liabilities under its clearing and settlement exchange sponsorship arrangements [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-26-000060::PART_II.Item_6#0145]. In summary, while regulatory engagement is an ongoing feature of BNY's operating environment, no material issues have been disclosed that are expected to result in a material adverse outcome.",
